 Cerebos has created this easy, mouth-watering recipe that is sure to be a crowd pleaser. Whether you’re cooking for your family, special someone or simply want to treat yourself, look no further. Let’s get cooking! READ: Goat cheese pita toasts with pomegranate pistachio and mint Ingredients: 10g dry yeast 5ml sugar 125ml warm water 4 cups flour 5ml Cerebos Mediterranean Sea Salt Flakes 15ml freshly chopped herbs 125ml warm milk 125ml warm water 60ml sunflower oil Your choice of: Cerebos Mediterranean Sea Salt Flakes Olives Herbs Sundried tomatoes READ: Grab a bottle of Jack Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 180°c. 2. Mix yeast, sugar and warm water and leave to stand and froth. 3. Place all the other ingredients in a mixing bowl, add the yeast mixture and mix with the dough hook of an electric mixer for 10 minutes. 4. Place in an oiled bowl and leave to double in size. 5. Knock the dough back and press into rounds on a baking tray. 6. Brush with oil and sprinkle with Cerebos Mediterranean Sea Salt Flakes. Allow to rise. You can add olive, herbs or sundried tomatoes at this stage. Be as creative as you wish, then bake at 180°c for 30-45 minutes until golden brown. 7. Serve with Mediterranean dips, olive oil and balsamic vinegar.